---

Closing Statement

ORL-AI explores a fundamental possibility:

Decision systems can resolve outcomes from structure, not from time, order, or synchronization.

It is released openly to encourage:

independent validation
real-world testing
safe experimentation
broader adoption of structure-first decision systems

Decision-making, traditionally governed by sequence, timing, and coordination, may also be understood as a process of structural resolution.

ORL-AI is offered as a reference model for that shift.
